'''Kameyama Hachimangu''' (かめやまはちまんぐう) is a [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sasebo City|ja|佐世保市|12=draft}}. Known locally as "Hachiman Shrine" or "Hachiman-sama," it is the largest shrine in the city.

== Overview ==
The shrine is located in the center of Sasebo City, northeast of the {{ill|Sasebo City Hall|ja|佐世保市役所|12=draft}} and across from National Route 204. It is the only {{ill|Beppyo shrines|ja|別表神社|12=draft}} in the city.

Within the grounds, there are a total of seven auxiliary shrines, including the Kameyama Inari Shrine.

== History ==
According to the shrine's tradition, it began in the 4th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|12=draft}} ({{ill|Hakuhō period|ja|白鳳|12=draft}}) when a {{ill|divine message|ja|神託|12=draft}} led to the transfer of spirits from [[Usa Jingū]]

From the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|12=draft}} onwards, it became a guardian shrine for the naval personnel of the {{ill|Sasebo Naval District|ja|軍港佐世保|12=draft}}, but the shrine buildings were destroyed during the {{ill|Sasebo Air Raid|ja|佐世保空襲|12=draft}} on June 29, 1945. The current buildings were rebuilt in 1964 using reinforced concrete.

Before World War II, it was finally ranked as a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|12=draft}}, and after the war, it became a Beppyo shrine of the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|12=draft}}.

== Deities ==
*{{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|12=draft}}
*{{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|仲哀天皇|12=draft}}
*{{ill|Empress Jingū|ja|神功皇后|12=draft}}
*{{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|12=draft}}
*{{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食神|12=draft}}

== Events ==
[[File:Kameyama hachimangu shrine Summer festival.JPG|thumbnail|right|Kameyama Hachimangu Summer festival]]
*Hatsumode, Coming-of-Age ceremony, Omiyamairi, {{ill|Shichi-Go-San|ja|七五三参り|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sasebo Kunchi|ja|佐世保くんち|12=draft}}
*Summer festival - Held from August 1 to 3. Stalls and vendors are set up along the approach, and dances are performed on the stage within the shrine grounds. Until around 2010, fireworks were launched from the grounds of the adjacent {{ill|Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|ja|長崎県立佐世保北中学校・高等学校|12=draft}} at 9 PM on the first and last days, and Niagara fireworks were lit within the shrine grounds.

