'''Kameyama Hachimangu''' (かめやまはちまんぐう) is a [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sasebo City|ja|佐世保市|12=draft|12=draft}}. Known locally as "Hachiman Shrine" or "Hachiman-sama," it is the largest shrine in the city.

== Overview ==
The shrine is located in the center of Sasebo City, northeast of the {{ill|Sasebo City Hall|ja|佐世保市役所|12=draft|12=draft}} and across from National Route 204. It is the only {{ill|Beppyo shrines|ja|別表神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in the city.

Within the grounds, there are a total of seven auxiliary shrines, including the Kameyama Inari Shrine.

== History ==
According to the shrine's tradition, it began in the 4th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Hakuhō period|ja|白鳳|12=draft|12=draft}}) when a {{ill|divine message|ja|神託|1=Oracle|12=draft|12=draft}} led to the transfer of spirits from [[Usa Jingū]]

From the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|12=draft|12=draft}} onwards, it became a guardian shrine for the naval personnel of the {{ill|Sasebo Naval District|ja|軍港佐世保|12=draft|12=draft}}, but the shrine buildings were destroyed during the {{ill|Sasebo Air Raid|ja|佐世保空襲|12=draft|12=draft}} on June 29, 1945. The current buildings were rebuilt in 1964 using reinforced concrete.

Before World War II, it was finally ranked as a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|12=draft|12=draft}}, and after the war, it became a Beppyo shrine of the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|12=draft|12=draft}}.

