'''Kameyama Hachimangu''' (かめやまはちまんぐう) is a [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Sasebo City|ja|佐世保市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo City|qq=}}. Known locally as "Hachiman Shrine" or "Hachiman-sama," it is the largest shrine in the city.

== Overview ==
The shrine is located in the center of Sasebo City, northeast of the {{ill|Sasebo City Hall|ja|佐世保市役所|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo City Hall|qq=}} and across from National Route 204. It is the only {{ill|Beppyo shrines|ja|別表神社|1=Beppyo Shrine|2=ja|3=別表神社|4=simple|5=Beppyo shrine|6=zh|7=別表神社|8=mr|9=बेप्प्यो तीर्थ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppyo shrines|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppyo Shrine|qq=}} in the city.

Within the grounds, there are a total of seven auxiliary shrines, including the Kameyama Inari Shrine.

== History ==
According to the shrine's tradition, it began in the 4th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} ({{ill|Hakuhō period|ja|白鳳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakuhō period|qq=}}) when a {{ill|divine message|ja|神託|1=Oracle|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/divine message|13=User:Immanuelle/Oracle|qq=}} led to the transfer of spirits from [[Usa Jingū]]

From the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}} onwards, it became a guardian shrine for the naval personnel of the {{ill|Sasebo Naval District|ja|軍港佐世保|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Naval District|qq=}}, but the shrine buildings were destroyed during the {{ill|Sasebo Air Raid|ja|佐世保空襲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Air Raid|qq=}} on June 29, 1945. The current buildings were rebuilt in 1964 using reinforced concrete.

Before World War II, it was finally Ranked as a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural shrine|qq=}}, and after the war, it became a Beppyo shrine of the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Association of Shinto Shrines|qq=}}.

== Deities ==
*{{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ōjin|qq=}}
*{{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|仲哀天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Chūai|qq=}}
*{{ill|Empress Jingū|ja|神功皇后|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Jingū|qq=}}
*{{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Nintoku|qq=}}
*{{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食神|1=Ukemochi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukemochi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukemochi|qq=}}

== Events ==
[[File:Kameyama hachimangu shrine Summer festival.JPG|thumbnail|right|Kameyama Hachimangu Summer festival]]
*Hatsumode, Coming-of-Age ceremony, Omiyamairi, {{ill|Shichi-Go-San|ja|七五三参り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichi-Go-San|qq=}}, {{ill|Sasebo Kunchi|ja|佐世保くんち|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Kunchi|qq=}}
*Summer festival - Held from August 1 to 3. Stalls and vendors are set up along the approach, and dances are performed on the stage within the shrine grounds. Until around 2010, fireworks were launched from the grounds of the adjacent {{ill|Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|ja|長崎県立佐世保北中学校・高等学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|qq=}} at 9 PM on the first and last days, and Niagara fireworks were lit within the shrine grounds.

== Access ==
*{{ill|Saihi Motor|ja|西肥自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saihi Motor|qq=}} (including {{ill|Sasebo Bus|ja|させぼバス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Bus|qq=}}) Get off at "Sasebo City Hall"
*{{ill|Matsuura Railway|ja|松浦鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsuura Railway|qq=}} {{ill|Nishi-Kyushu Line|ja|西九州線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishi-Kyushu Line|qq=}} Get off at "Kita-Sasebo Station", 8 minutes on foot

