== Events ==
[[File:Kameyama hachimangu shrine Summer festival.JPG|thumbnail|right|Kameyama Hachimangu Summer festival]]
*Hatsumode, Coming-of-Age ceremony, Omiyamairi, {{ill|Shichi-Go-San|ja|七五三参り|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shichi-Go-San|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Sasebo Kunchi|ja|佐世保くんち|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Kunchi|1=Q11382501|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11382501}}
*Summer festival - Held from August 1 to 3. Stalls and vendors are set up along the approach, and dances are performed on the stage within the shrine grounds. Until around 2010, fireworks were launched from the grounds of the adjacent {{ill|Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|ja|長崎県立佐世保北中学校・高等学校|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|1=Sasebo Kita Junior High and High School|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11652682}} at 9 PM on the first and last days, and Niagara fireworks were lit within the shrine grounds.

== Access ==
*{{ill|Saihi Motor|en|Saihi Motor|qid=Q7400098|lt=Saihi Motor|1=Saihi Bus}} (including {{ill|Sasebo Bus|ja|させぼバス|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasebo Bus|1=Sasebo Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11267964}}) Get off at "Sasebo City Hall"
*{{ill|Matsuura Railway|en|Matsuura Railway|qid=Q6788223|lt=Matsuura Railway|1=Matsuura Railway}} {{ill|Nishi-Kyushu Line|ja|西九州線|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishi-Kyushu Line|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 松浦鉄道西九州線|1=Nishi-Kyūshū Line|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q7040371}} Get off at "Kita-Sasebo Station", 8 minutes on foot

